variable.length() gives you the length 
variable.empty() if you give an empty input on the string 
variable.clear() clears the name 
variable.appeend( add to end of string ) adds the argument given into the end of the string
variable.at(index) returns the index in the string like index = 0 that means the first letter  
variable.insert(index, what you want to replace with) replaces the index with what you want to add 
variable.find( what you wnt to find) tells you the first index of what you want to find 
variable.erase (beginning index, ending index) erases between the indx 